\pard\li720\sa160\sl240\slmult1\tx990\par

\pard\li360\sl240\slmult1\b LRC-1 \f2\endash\f0  2,000-FOOT RESTRICTIVE AERIAL EASEMENT\par
\b0 The Lessor further agrees for the term of this lease, or any renewal term thereof, to refrain from or prohibit the placing of any obstruction on Lessor\rquote s property within 2,000 feet of the center of the facility, \cf1 as shown on Exhibit \ldblquote A\rdblquote , \cf0 with the understanding that such restriction does not prohibit the use of the restricted area for the grazing of livestock or for other agricultural purposes.  The Lessor hereby grants the Government the right to clear and continue to clear trees or other obstructions in the restricted area during the term of this lease and any renewal thereof.  For the purpose of this provision, an obstruction is defined as any object which projects seventy-five (75) feet or more above the ground surface within the restricted area which would adversely affect the operation of the air navigation facility installed by the Government.  In the event any wire fence or fences within the restricted area are considered to be an obstruction to the proper operations of the air navigation facility installed, the Government is granted the right and privilege to remove said wire fence or fences, and replace same with a wooden fence, all at the expense of the Government.  \par
